PARAGRAPH.#text: American Tower Corp. AMT swung to a third-quarter profit as the cell-tower real-estate investment trust booked a foreign-currency related gain. The company also said it expects to acquire up to 700 communications sites globally during the fourth quarter. American Tower, with cell-tower sites in the U.S. and around the world, has steadily posted double-digit revenue growth amid strong demand for broadband-data services in the U.S. The company converted to a REIT late last year. Cell-tower companies benefit as volume increases, prompting wireless carriers to spend more to upgrade equipment.

Headlines.Headline: Crown Castle Profit Falls 18% amid Higher Tax Provision

PARAGRAPH.#text: Crown Castle International Corp.'s CCI third-quarter earnings fell 18% as the cell-tower company was hit with a sharply higher tax provision, masking revenue growth. For the year, the company raised its per-share earnings estimate to 75 cents to 90 cents, from its July estimate for 71 cents to 96 cents. For the current quarter, the company forecast per-share earnings of five cents to 17 cents. Analysts polled by Thomson Reuters most recently expected 15 cents. For 2013 Crown Castle projected per-share earnings of 24 cents to 62 cents.
